<item>
            <title>[PIG-3894] Datetime function AddDuration, SubtractDuration and all Between functions don&apos;t check for null values in the input tuple.</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/PIG-3894</link>
                <project id="12310730" key="PIG">Pig</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The simple datetime functions: GetMonth, GetHour, ToDate, GetYear etc all have safe treatment of null values in the input tuple.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;e.g.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-style: solid;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeHeader panelHeader&quot; style=&quot;border-bottom-width: 1px;border-bottom-style: solid;&quot;&gt;&lt;b&gt;GetMonth.java&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;@Override
&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;public&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;Integer&lt;/span&gt; exec(Tuple input) &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;throws&lt;/span&gt; IOException {
    &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;if&lt;/span&gt; (input == &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;null&lt;/span&gt; || input.size() &amp;lt; 1 || input.get(0) == &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;null&lt;/span&gt;) {
        &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;return&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;null&lt;/span&gt;;
    }
    &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;return&lt;/span&gt; ((DateTime) input.get(0)).getMonthOfYear();
}
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;However, all of the &quot;Duration&quot; or &quot;Between&quot; functions are missing this null-checking, and so fail completely when the are passed tuples with null values.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;e.g.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-style: solid;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeHeader panelHeader&quot; style=&quot;border-bottom-width: 1px;border-bottom-style: solid;&quot;&gt;&lt;b&gt;AddDuration.java&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;@Override
&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;public&lt;/span&gt; DateTime exec(Tuple input) &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;throws&lt;/span&gt; IOException {
    &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;if&lt;/span&gt; (input == &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;null&lt;/span&gt; || input.size() &amp;lt; 2) {
        &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;return&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;null&lt;/span&gt;;
    }
    &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;return&lt;/span&gt; ((DateTime) input.get(0)).plus(&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;new&lt;/span&gt; Period((&lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;String&lt;/span&gt;) input.get(1)));
}
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This is inconsistent, problematic and easy to fix.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
